So the fixed code would be:

private void visitNew(NodeTraversal t, Node n) {
  Node constructor = n.getFirstChild();
  JSType type = getJSType(constructor).restrictByNotNullOrUndefined();
  if (type.isFunctionType() && type.toMaybeFunctionType().isConstructor()) {
    FunctionType fnType = type.toMaybeFunctionType();
    visitParameterList(t, n, fnType);
    ensureTyped(t, n, fnType.getInstanceType());
  } else if (type.isEmptyType() || type.isUnknownType()) {
    ensureTyped(t, n);
  } else {
    report(t, n, NOT_A_CONSTRUCTOR);
    ensureTyped(t, n);
  }
}

This preserves the behavior for empty/unknown types (they go to the middle branch) but for non-function types that claim to be constructors, they will be reported as NOT_A_CONSTRUCTOR. However, this changes behavior: previously, if `type.isConstructor()` was true but `toMaybeFunctionType()` returned null, it would go to the inner else and not report error. Now it would go to the outer else and report error. That might be the intended fix.

